76561198042526657,Not Recommended,416060,31413213,Posted: 28 April,all,the_immortal,"Well. What can i say about this game.Visuals/atmosphere/sound: 5/5.Controls: 0/5That's probably it. The game by itself is something Fallout'ish / Deus ex like, but it's got completely different game mechanics.  It's all real time. You control character by mouse only. No tactical time stop, no bullet time. And i should say - the controls are STIFF. It takes an eternity before character starts to do what you want it to do. And that what gives this game it's difficulty. Your ability to react in combat is significantly limited. This turns every combat in to a roulette. If you're lucky enough, you can bring down a bunch of enemies and don't get a scratch. It not - you are dead. However - you have stuff to mitigate it - active abilities. But they have really beefy cooldown times. Now multiply that by: no saves through the mission, not even on game exit, no checkpoints. You died - you start it over. And missions are pretty big if you do all the side stuff. Add limited supplies. So your win strategy is: run into bunch of enemies, use cooldowns. Wait for cooldowns to reset. Repeat. That makes game reeeally hardcore.So at a time i have pretty mixed feelings about this game. Visuals are really good. Combat is actually satisfying. It's got a lot of RPG in it, and i really like RPG. But difficulty through controls is really killing most of the fun for me. A good example of great indie cyberpunk/RPG is Dex. And that game is not easy either. But the big difference - it is really responsive. I actually enjoyed playing it. And it's really sad about this game. It has really big potential in it. Fix controls, add saves/checkpoints - 5/5."
,Recommended,416060,32962748,Posted: 28 June,all,Redrusty66,"Fantastic isometric title. The dark and quasi cyberpunk atmosphere is very alluring. The story is familiar in one way or anotherm There are over 12 billion people and not enough usable fresh water for them. The global corporation, SICON, is in charge of what's left, and the world isn't happy about it. You take control of one of three mercenaries for hire and carry out various paid missions concerning SICON, usually by shooting everything in sight. This game does need serious control-work. It's the only thing really about the game that causes any distress at all, and casn on oocasion steal a bit of your joy. You can see many complaints in the reviews, almost all of them about this one issue. I would hope the developers are smart enough to get off their asses and do something about, if they would, this game could go down in iconic history as one of the best of its genre.I found it both smooth and bugkess (That I noticed anyway), plenty of room for immersion and scratches pretty much every isometric itch I have. Very good price for a game of this level of quality, if oyu are into the genre.  If you're a fan of any of the relvant genres, ARPG, isometric, quasi-top down-ish, fallout-style shorters...ect,ect. This is certianly a game you should have in your library."
