76561198021432764,Recommended,416060,34297609,Posted: 16 August,all,joshgordon79,"I've played about 10 minutes so far, but thought I'd give my initial impressions.Overall, I like the game so far.  It reminds me a bit of the old Syndicate game set in a CyberPunk type, corporations rule the world way.  The English is a little rough.  That is to say, it's about 99% understandable, but also fairly obvious that it was translated by a non-speaker.  The game is pretty unforgiving when it comes to combat, even on Easy difficulty.  As far as I can find, there's no pause or anything when fighting.  And if you get tag teamed by 2 or 3 guys, you're probably going to die, at least at the start (this is not a negative in my opinion -- that's they way it should be).A few things I don't like so far:1.  You can quick save, but you can't get to a main menu screen unless you quit out of the game.  That's pretty bad.2.  There's no tutorial at all.  There are a few helpful boxes that pop up, but they're not all that great.  Spend some time looking at the controls before you start playing.3.  I realize it's cyberpunk, but the world is basically monotone (gray).  Skills and map are colored, but still not enough to liven things up much.I'll keep you posted on my 2nd and 3rd impressions after I play for a few hours and get some experience with it."
